        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should healthcare providers show pricing on their websites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Healthcare pricing transparency varies by specialty and practice model. For therapists and counselors: showing session rates ($150-250 per session) increases qualified inquiries by 40%. Patients self-select based on budget, saving everyone time. For medical practices: less common to show pricing due to insurance complexity. Better to show: insurance plans accepted, typical visit costs by insurance tier, payment policies, and financing options. For elective procedures (cosmetic dentistry, plastic surgery, med spa): show pricing ranges prominently since patients comparison shop. For cash-pay services (acupuncture, massage, coaching): show clear pricing. Best practice: indicate your pricing approach (insurance vs cash-pay), show accepted insurance plans, provide payment policy information, and include contact option for specific pricing questions. Transparency builds trust and reduces administrative burden."
